This paper deals with the distribution and conception of knowledge, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses mathematical theories such as Formal Concept Analysis and Information Flow, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the categorical equivalence between classifications and concept lattices, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
